node.text:
It was our profound honor to have a conversation with @ken.wilber.official & @sebastiansiegel1 about the new film Grace & Grit. Ken authored the deeply moving story, Grace & Grit, about his late wife Treya and their transcendental love. Sebastian adapted and directed Ken’s book for the screen and it is newly released. Allyson and I have loved Ken as a friend and Integral philosopher for decades and it went deep. Ken speaks candidly of suffering and spiritual opening, an important reminder in these traumatic times.  Ken Wilber’s integral view is incredibly helpful to analyze, expand, and reach for one's highest potential. I know many people who feel the same way. Eternally grateful for sharing your vision with us, Ken and for this new way of people getting to know Ken and Treya through Sebastian Siegel’s new motion picture Grace & Grit.

Watch our CoSM Podcast episode with  @ken.wilber.official and @sebastiansiegel1 and @allysongreycosm >> https://youtu.be/VtE84c9s2QY

node.title: CoSM Podcast: Ken Wilber & Sebastian Siegel on Grace & Grit

node.text:
Back in 1978, Allyson @allysongreycosm  recommended that I create detailed paintings inviting the viewer to “mirror” and identify with a comprehensive map of body, mind and spirit. Allyson later titled the series Sacred Mirrors. With figures transforming through mystic dimensions of awareness, the artwork was always intended for mind expanding and healing contemplation. We are so grateful to the CoSM team and worldwide community that the Sacred Mirrors are now installed in a Chapel in Entheon. ⠀

node.text:
Divine Imagination overflows with numinous flora and fauna, an endless well of patterns springing from a single paisley mustard seed, spirallically growing, interweaving, disobeying the gravity of death and spreading via the visionary domain throughout world culture. The inner realms undulate with infinite iridescent swirls and artists of all times, everywhere, labor to express a fragment of the fantastic richness, immersed in the elemental flow of life, the cascade of rivers and clouds, the rhythm of mountains and valleys, the swirl of flames and galaxies.⠀
⠀

@allysongreycosm & I will be showing 45 works, some rarely or never before seen in a gallery show at the Mesa Art Center in Arizona @mesaartscenter from September 10, 2021 through January 23, 2022.
